condition.narrative: Section I. A. 1. Institutional ArrangementsIn order to facilitate the carrying-out of the Project, the Recipient shall maintain,at all times during the implementation of the Project, a dedicated Project Steering Committee within the Ministry of Education(MOE), supported by a dedicated secretariat, with functions and resources satisfactory to the Association, and with staff inadequate numbers and with qualifications, experience and terms of reference satisfactory to the Association.

Section I. B. 1. Project Operational ManualThe Recipient shall ensure that the Project is carried out in accordance with thearrangements and procedures set out in the Project Operational Manual (provided, however, that in the case of any conflict betweenthe arrangements and procedures set out in the said manual and the provisions of this Agreement, the provisions of this Agreementshall prevail) and, except as the Association shall otherwise agree, shall not amend, abrogate or waive any provision of the saidmanual.

Section I. B. 2. Operational GuidelinesThe Recipient shall: (a) prior to financing any grants out of the proceeds of theFinancing under the School Improvement Support Program (SISP), the Education for Children on the Move Program (ECMP), and theAlternative Education Program (AEP), adopt Operational Guidelines (OGs) for said programs, in form and substance satisfactory tothe Association, detailing the eligibility criteria and approval and administration arrangements for the provision of grants,including environmental and social safeguard arrangements consistent with the provisions of Part C of Schedule I; and (b)thereafter ensure that all grants financed out of the proceeds of the Financing are made and administered in accordance with saidOperational Guidelines (provided, however, that in the case of any conflict between the arrangements and procedures set out in thesaid guidelines and the provisions of the Financing Agreement (FA), the provisions of the FA shall prevail); and (c) except as theAssociation shall otherwise agree, not amend, abrogate or waive any provision of the OGs.

Section I. C. 1 (a) SafeguardsThe Project is carried out with due regard to appropriate health, safety, social, and environmentalpractices and standards, and in accordance with the Safeguards Instruments.

Section I. C. 3. SafeguardsThe Recipient shall: (a) not take any action within its control to restrict movement of ProjectBeneficiaries so as to adversely affect their ability to access and benefit from Project activities and facilities; and (b) takeall actions within its control to remove restrictions on movement that adversely affect Project Beneficiaries’ ability to accessand benefit from Project activities and facilities.

Section I. D. School Improvement Fund and Alternative Education FundThe Recipient shall ensure that targeted school and centerswill only be eligible for receiving School Improvement Funds (SIF) or Alternative Education Funds (AEF) after they have met theeligibility criteria and complied with the requirements specified in the School Improvement Support Program (SISP), Education forChildren on the Move Program (ECMP), and Alternative Education Program (AEP) OGs, the Community Participation Planning Framework(CPPF), and Community Participation Plans (CPPs) provided, however, that in the case of any conflict between the arrangements andprocedures set out in the said OGs and CPPF/CPPs and the provisions of the FA, the provisions of the FA shall prevail) and, exceptas the Association shall otherwise agree, shall not amend, abrogate or waive any provision of the said OGs and CPPF/CPPs.

Section II. B. DLI Monitoring and ReportingWithout limitation on its general reporting obligations under Part A ("The Recipientshall furnish to the Association each Project Report for Part 4 of the Project not later than December 31 of each Fiscal Year,covering such year"), the Recipient shall monitor and furnish reports to the Association on the achievement of the DLI Targets, notlater than July 31 and January 31 of each year during the implementation of the Project, except for the first report which shall befurnished to the Association not later than three (3) months after effectiveness of the FA, in accordance with the verificationprotocol set out in the Project Operational Manual.

Section II. C. Access to Project Sites and Information Pursuant to, and without limitation upon, the provisions of Section 5.11of the General Conditions of the FA, the Recipient shall ensure that the Association, including its staff, consultants or any otherrepresentatives, are provided prompt, safe and unimpeded access to Buthidaung, Maungdaw and Yathedaung (BMY) and any other parts ofthe Recipient’s territory for purposes related to the supervision of Project activities and verification of DLIs in accordance withthe provisions of the FA, including the provision of all relevant documents and information required for such purposes.
